reviews.text: This was a fun tour. The tour guide was a former miner there and full of interesting stories. The length of the tour was perfect. Not too long, not too short. Not difficult for people with mobility issues. The hardest part of the tour was sitting on the trolley to get on and out. But it goes by quickly.

This was a super fun way to spend time in Bisbee.  Make sure you get there early to reserve a spot as it seems like the tickets (on weekends anyways) sell out one or two tours early.  The tour guide was very informative, and pretty funny in a 'dad joke' kind of way.    I'm not sure I'd take the tour more than once unless they opened up a new part of the mine, but I would definitely recommend it to anyone who hasn't done it before.
Enjoyed the tour. Would have liked to see more. Great guide. Presentation given as if we were the working miners. Great touch.
Very interesting and interactive tour. A fun journey into the old mine. Definitely a must see if you are in Bisbee.

We had such a great time as a family here.  Our guide was a former miner who answered all kinds of background questions for us.  We learned about how they originally cut into the mountain by hand swung hammers all the way through the mine being shut down due to the increase in lumber cost and drop in copper prices.

I was here 15 years ago and not much has changed as far as the lavender pit. While the sides are starting to have mudslides, a reasonable person could see that there use to be roads doing from top to bottom. Great place to stop and stretch.
Great place. The view here is amazing. I get to drive past this every other week. The little pond at the bottom makes me wonder if thier is anything living in it.
I thought the Peep Holes in the fence was a great idea. Got good photos.
It's a neat pit. Beautiful mineral colors and an informative sign about the history and composition. There's a nice WWII monument here also.

This is an old copper mine in Bisbee Arizona.
It is a unique sight to see if you're  in the area.
I wouldn't driveway out of my way just to see it.

HUGE pancakes. California omelet was great too. We got seated with a short wait, but the line was pretty long when we left.
Service is good. Coffee is good. Amenities bare bones. I thought it was a little pricey. But that is the TRENDY TREND. 
Seems like a very popular place. Cool area. Rusty cars and motorcycles.

Awesome breakfast place hidden within an old like town. It’s a great place to pop in the morning for eggs or pancakes. The bottomless filter coffee and people watching pair very well. A good escape from Sierra Vista.

This is the original one in Bisbee, "Just past the pit".
Do not stop here if you are not that hungry. Do stop in if you want healthy portions of stick to your ribs American diner style foods and bottomless coffee. Our group got the potato cakes, Erie St club, Gooey Louie, and biscuits and gravy. Wow! What a spread. Everyone was full and happy and ready for a nap.
Great place customer service was great. Good food. I loved the biscuits and gravy.

Been here and the Tucson locations several times. I recall the Bisbee location being much better. Service good as always but the potatoes (both kinds) were very under-done and starchy. The rest of breakfast was good, but not excellent. Will try again next time we are in town.

Amazing! Every bite of every course was perfect. A bargain besides. My duck was absolutely perfect. And my wife's special request, lamb chops which had left the menu, was excellent. Wonderful service. Nice atmosphere.  I would take off 1/10 of a star for lack of espresso. ;-) We're planning at least one more meal at Cafe Roka before we leave. Highly recommended.

EDIT: Went back for a second meal. Equally wonderful!

Loved it! The staff were amazing. Very professional and fun! We had a fun 4 course meal and loved it. The menu changes regularly to make it more exciting. There are multiple levels to the cafe and each level is nicely decorated and it adds a lot to the ambience. Looking forward to going back! 

Only warning I have would be to go there with money to spend. It is a little pricey. But, it's well worth it.

Cafe Roka is a great dining experience! An innovative menu, great bar & wine selection and first class service, plus live jazz make this our go to place for special occasions. Prices are also reasonable for what you get. The place to go in Cochise county.
Spectacular fine dining in Bisbee.  Service is fantastic and the food is even better.  Sit at the bar for great conversation with Fred who makes the best handcrafted cocktails!
Can be a bit pricey. Two of us had one drink each, an entree, and a dessert each. Spent just over $100 without tip. The food and drinks were excellent and worth every penny.

The food was very good. It was price kind of high that overall very tasty. there is no weight staff here so you order at the counter and they give you a number then it delivered to your table. Then you take the slip up to the cashier and pay for your meal which was okay. You could hardly see the cashier because of all the we take tip signs and please tip but overall the experience was good and yes I did tip the kitchen staff.

I love the food here and the smoothies are wonderful. If you’re dining in, all the sandwiches come with a salad & house-made balsamic dressing!! The gluten-free bread here is the best I’ve ever had. I’ve also tried some of their cookies and they were all bomb. Ambiance is good. The staff usually seem a bit stressed, but probably because this place is always busy. Have your order ready at the counter and you’re golden.

I saved this store excited to visit it. Talk about disappointing. Mainly due to the people who worked there.  No hello, nothing, which is okay. I was looking at the baked goods which looked amazing. As I was, the woman behind the counter barked out that we could seat ourselves at the tables. I told her I just wanted a scone. Her reply was, the cash register was "over there,"  she'd get to us in a second. " Then she proceeded to ignore us and a younger woman came over and helped.  Everyone was so rude. Would never stop there again.

Exceptional service, exceptional home prepared foods, great Bisbee atmosphere.  Pull up a table and get the local knowledge from friendly, long time residents. Best homemade soups and daily delicacies in Southern Arizona.

Everytime I arrive here, pleasant surprises await me. Superb, affordable, homemade hot entrees, soups, salads and sandwiches are freshly and creatively made. Food is absolutely scrumptious! Their market provides unique varieties of upscale packaged food items. Beautiful pillows are available, as well as ice cream cones. A remarkable place to shop.

The antipasto platter was stunning with so much and of such a variety that it would have sufficed for the meal.  But no -we also had full dinners - from luscious veal's through several pastas - that were equally delicious and gorgeous.  It is a byob place so bring your own wine.  That makes this place a bargain because you don't have to pay the exorbitant restaurateur markup on the wine.  There is a liquor store right next door - very convenient.  The staff was charming as was the interior decor.  Four of us dined the last time and now coming back in a few weeks with a party of 10.
Rosa's is an excellent place to dine for italian cuisine. A small, intimate restaurant, perfect for couples!

I went to Rosas about two years aso. It was excellent and the food was great however this time we encountered...BAD service! Bad food! BAD staff! We went to Rosas to celebrate a special occassion. Needless to say it was ruied with BAD attitudes of the staff. Stale bread, over cooked pasta and worst of all was the bickering between the staff right in front of us. How can you entrust your food to people who dont even get along. And even after all this I paid the bill but will never return again!
They are now closed.

Okay selection but prices seemed to vary wildly between being on point, a good deal, and way too expensive. Didn't seem to be set up like an actual Food Co-op, either. Did have great options for healthy dog food that wasn't terribly expensive, and even had some bread CBD products. Know they closed not long after we last went but not sure if they've reopened yet. Hopefully they come back with better organization. Staff was always super friendly to us. Always very clean as well. Had Jun Honey Kombucha (AZ Company) which is always a plus.

I shop here almost every day and the staff goes the extra mile to try to keep the merchandise I love on hand. Even with their limitations as a small business who cannot get discounts for volume, they always have a good variety of items on the shelf, seasonal organic and locally grown vegetables and nice ready-to-eat choices from the deli.
Went out of business due to Incompetant board of directors
Nothing to see here.

This is our main store for shopping close to home! It can be pretty spendy at times with prices, but with Just4U coupons help a lot!! They have some great deals at times. If you want quality and a variety even with Safeway brands  Safeway is great for that. They have a deli, bakery and pharmacy. They also have a Starbucks inside. The one complaint I have lately with them is their meat department. The quality of their meat isn't as great as it use to be. We've found bone grit on the pork and bones in boneless skinless chicken. Otherwise I love their produce, breads, desserts and products!! Plus you'll always get GREAT customer service and asked if you need help out!! Or you can also do self checkout instead.

All and all it's not a bad place to shop... it's a little spendy... you definitely need to watch for deals... The cashiers are pretty nice..The pharmacy and their employees are Rock Stars... Trevor is one of the pharmacist who always goes above and beyond to take care of your needs... Thank you ever so much Trevor... yes, Amy your pretty awesome... Thank you kindly... :-) :-) :-)

This store is brightly lit and well maintained. We usually go to Costco for a lot of reasons but for small and unique grocery purchases we end up at Safeway. The checkers at this location are almost always pleasant and attentive, both things that aren't always guaranteed these days.
Its a grocery store chain. The quality is good. The price is a little high, but they offer a membership discount.

The old lady in the deli is absolutely the rudest person I’ve ever met in my life she constantly makes you feel like your bothering her that you want a sandwhich rolled her eyes and got huffy puffy that I asked for bacon and proceeded to say “I guess, but that’s gonna cost more” (like I didn’t already know that) then didn’t ask me if I wanted anything else threw my snadwhich on the counter and walked away. I will never be going back there again so disappointed
